sections.title: MBBS Admission in Maharashtra 2025-26, Colleges Seat Matrix, Fee Structure, Application process, cut-off and Counselling

content.content: Maharashtra is a bustling center of industry, innovation, and education, celebrated for its vibrant culture, storied past, and significant economic contributions to India. Its capital.

Renowned as a premier destination for medical education in India, Maharashtra offers a plethora of undergraduate and postgraduate medical programs, drawing students from all corners of the nation. Admission to MBBS programs in Maharashtra is conducted through the NEET exam, with successful candidates participating in state counseling for enrollment.

The MBBS curriculum in Maharashtra spans 5.5 years, comprising 4.5 years of academic study and 1 year of compulsory internship, providing students with comprehensive training and practical experience.In Maharashtra aspiring MBBS students have a variety of options available for admission. The state boasts both government and private medical colleges and universities. Typically, securing admission into government medical colleges is more competitive than private ones, resulting in higher cut-off marks for government institutions.

The total number of MBBS seats in Maharashtra can vary each year due to factors such as government policies, changes in infrastructure, and accreditation of new medical colleges. For MBBS Admission Maharashtra 2025 total 10845  seats are available in Government and private Medical Colleges. The state has 1 AIIMS located at Nagpur and 32 Government and 36 Private Medical Colleges.

In the following sections, we will delve into the specifics of MBBS admission for the academic year 2025-26 in Maharashtra including details on college seat matrix, fee structure, application process, cut-off marks, and counseling procedures. For personalized assistance with MBBS admission in India or abroad, feel free to reach out to our dedicated admission counseling team at MBBS APP.

Maharashtra has a total of 68 medical colleges, including 30 government medical colleges, 1 AIIMS (All India Institute of Medical Sciences), 1 central universities, 12 Deemed university and 24 private medical colleges. The government medical colleges offer 5125 MBBS seats, while the private medical colleges offer 5720 MBBS seats.

content.content: The NEET cutoff is determined based on various factors such as the number of applicants, the difficulty level of the exam, and the availability of seats in medical and dental colleges. Generally, higher cutoffs are seen in prestigious colleges and for popular courses. It’s crucial for aspiring medical students to keep track of cutoff trends and prepare accordingly

sections.title: Application Process for MBBS Admission Maharashtra

content.content: The Commissioner, State CET CELL, Mumbai will conduct the admission process for all the Health Science courses in the State of Maharashtra. Online applications will be invited from eligible candidate(s) for admission to all Government/Corporation, Private & Minority Colleges. Online application form will be made available on website www.mahacet.org.

content.list:
• Admission processing Fee: Cost of online application form of NEET-UG 2023 is Rs. 1000/- for MBBS course of State quota, Rs 5000/- for Institutional quota of MBBS course only, and Rs. 6000/- for both quota of MBBS course only. This application fee is not refundable. It is sole responsibility of candidate to ascertain eligibility and also online payment of fees with in prescribed period, failing which online application will be rejected. 
  • The provisional State merit list for seats under State quota in Government / Corporation, Government Aided and all the quota seats in Private/ Minority colleges will be published on the website of State CET CELL as per constitutional and / or specified reservation claimed by candidate(s). The list of applicants will be prepared on the basis of information submitted by candidate(s) through online process made available on website www.mahacet.org. 
  • The provisional state merit list will be prepared on the basis of the information filled in the registration form and the documents uploaded by the Candidate. The verification of Original Documents shall be done by the admitting college authorities in which the candidate submits her/his documents for admission.
  • During online process, there will be choice for opting Institutional quota seats (15%) for MBBS course at Unaided Private / Minority colleges.
  • The admission process fee (non-refundable) for Institutional quota seats of MBBS will be Rs. 5000/-.
  • Admission will be on the basis of NEET UG 2023 rank and on All India basis including NRI, OMS & OCI.

• The candidate must be an Indian National.
  • The candidate must be registered with State CET cell, Mumbai through online application on website of State CET Cell.
  • Indian Citizen
  • Overseas Citizen of India (OCI) Candidate will be eligible for Government / Corporation / Government Aided / Private unaided college for academic year 2025-26.
  • Those who want to apply must have a 10+2 in the science stream from a recognized board.
  • Those who want to apply for Maharashtra MBBS Admission must have taken Biology as a required course and have a minimum of 50% overall marks.
  • Those who want to apply must take the NEET Exam. From the 2023–24 academic year on, there is no upper age limit to take the NEET exam.

sections.title: Document Required for MBBS Admission Maharashtra

content.list:
• Score Sheet for NEET 2024
  • NEET Admission Ticket
  • Letter of Assignment
  • 12th class card and passing certificate
  • Grade Card and Passing Certificate for Grade 10
  • All grade reports for classes 11 and 12, if they were passed in more than one attempt.
  • A copy of a photo identification card, such as a driver’s licence, PAN card, electoral card, government or public utility card, school ID card, or Aadhar card.
  • Valid caste certificate, sub-category certificate, if applicable
  • Certificate of domicile, if applicable
  • 4 passport size photographs same as affixed on application form
  • Character certification from the previous study institution
  • Migration Certificate from the previous study institution
  • The MBBS admission process in Maharashtra is a competitive one, but it is also a fair one. All candidates who meet the eligibility criteria have a chance to be admitted to a medical college in the state.
